      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(tui): fetch startup conversation summary dynamically from Gateway API",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: TUI startup summary lookup could include sessions from other agents and could run again after a Gateway reconnect.\n- Why it matters: reconnects should not add duplicate startup summaries, and an agent-scoped TUI should not preview unrelated agent sessions.\n- What changed: startup summary session lookup now uses current-agent listSessions params, excludes global/unknown sessions, and skips reconnect fetches.\n- What did NOT change: local mode still skips the Gateway summary fetch, and the summary remains best effort.\n\n## Change Type (select all)\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n- [x] Feature\n- [x] Refactor required for the fix\n- [ ] Docs\n- [ ] Security hardening\n- [ ] Chore/infra\n\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\n\n- [ ] Gateway / orchestration\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\n- [ ] Memory / storage\n- [ ] Integrations\n- [ ] API / contracts\n- [x] UI / DX\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\n\n## Linked Issue/PR\n\n- Fixes #71719\n- Related #\n- [x] This PR fixes a bug or regression\n\n## Root Cause (if applicable)\n\n- Root cause: the initial startup summary fetch was unscoped and only checked local mode, so it could read non-current agent sessions and repeat after reconnect.\n- Missing detection / guardrail: tests covered TUI startup behavior but not reconnect gating or current-agent session list params.\n- Contributing context: listSessions defaults include broader session scopes unless explicitly constrained.\n\n## Regression Test Plan (if applicable)\n\n- Coverage level that should have caught this:\n  - [x] Unit test\n  - [ ] Seam / integration test\n  - [ ] End-to-end test\n  - [ ] Existing coverage already sufficient\n- Target test or file: src/tui/tui.test.ts\n- Scenario the test should lock in: startup summary fetch only happens on first non-local connection and listSessions is scoped to the normalized current agent with global and unknown sessions excluded.\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: the bug is in TUI startup decision and request parameter construction, so focused unit tests cover the behavior without live Gateway or terminal interaction.\n- Existing test that already covers this (if any): related TUI command smoke coverage exists in src/cli/program.smoke.test.ts and TUI command handler coverage exists in src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts.\n- If no new test is added, why not: N/A, this PR adds targeted tests.\n\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\n\nWhen connecting to a Gateway, the TUI still displays a startup summary from recent history when available. The summary is now limited to the current agent and is not inserted again after a Gateway reconnect.\n\n## Diagram (if applicable)\n\nN/A\n\n## Security Impact (required)\n\n- New permissions/capabilities? No\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? No\n- New/changed network calls? No, this narrows the existing startup listSessions call.\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? No\n- Data access scope changed? Yes, narrowed to current-agent sessions and excludes global/unknown sessions.\n- If any Yes, explain risk + mitigation: data access is reduced, not expanded.\n\n## Repro + Verification\n\n### Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Runtime/container: Node.js via pnpm\n- Model/provider: N/A\n- Integration/channel (if any): TUI / Gateway client unit coverage\n- Relevant config (redacted): default test config\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Run pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/tui/tui.ts src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts CHANGELOG.md\n2. Run git diff --check\n3. Run pnpm test src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts src/cli/program.smoke.test.ts\n4. Run pnpm check:changed\n\n### Expected\n\n- Formatting, whitespace, targeted tests, and changed-lane checks pass.\n\n### Actual\n\n- All commands passed locally. The first sandboxed pnpm check:changed attempt hit spawnSync git EPERM, then the same command passed when rerun outside the sandbox.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: TUI startup summary fetch is scoped to the current agent and skipped on Gateway reconnect or local mode.\n- Real environment tested: Local Linux checkout of PR branch feature/dynamic-tui-summary at commit 5ca83b1860850a427e27fc07192f7b1e0687c02f, Node.js via repo toolchain.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: node --import tsx -e import the patched TUI helpers from ./src/tui/tui.ts and print the reconnect/local gating plus listSessions params for agent Work.\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal output from real checked-out PR code:\n\n    {\n      \"firstNonLocal\": true,\n      \"reconnect\": false,\n      \"local\": false,\n      \"params\": {\n        \"limit\": 10,\n        \"includeGlobal\": false,\n        \"includeUnknown\": false,\n        \"includeDerivedTitles\": true,\n        \"includeLastMessage\": true,\n        \"agentId\": \"work\"\n      }\n    }\n\n- Observed result after fix: The patched code fetches only on first non-local connection, skips reconnect, skips local mode, normalizes Work to work, and requests current-agent sessions while excluding global and unknown sessions.\n- What was not tested: Live interactive TUI rendering against the running Gateway was not exercised, to avoid disturbing the active OpenClaw session.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- [x] Failing test/log before + passing after\n- [x] Trace/log snippets\n- [ ] Screenshot/recording\n- [ ] Perf numbers (if relevant)\n\nLocal command evidence:\n\n- pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/tui/tui.ts src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts CHANGELOG.md: passed, all matched files use the correct format.\n- git diff --check: passed.\n- pnpm test src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts src/cli/program.smoke.test.ts: passed 2 Vitest shards in 31.36s.\n- pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.tui.config.ts src/tui/tui.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts src/cli/program.smoke.test.ts --reporter verbose: passed 2 files, 72 tests.\n- pnpm check:changed: passed after rerun outside sandbox due local spawnSync git EPERM in the sandbox.\n\n## Human Verification (required)\n\n- Verified scenarios: startup summary formatting, first-connect-only gating, current-agent listSessions params, targeted TUI test suite, changed-lane validation.\n- Edge cases checked: reconnect does not fetch, local mode does not fetch, mixed-case agent IDs normalize before listSessions.\n- What you did not verify: live interactive TUI rendering against a running Gateway, to avoid disturbing the active OpenClaw session.\n\n## Review Conversations\n\n- [x] I replied to or resolved every bot review conversation I addressed in this PR.\n- [ ] I left unresolved only the conversations that still need reviewer or maintainer judgment.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\n- Backward compatible? Yes\n- Config/env changes? No\n- Migration needed? No\n- If yes, exact upgrade steps: N/A\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n- Risk: startup summary could become narrower than some users expect if they relied on cross-agent previews.\n  - Mitigation: this is intentional for agent-scoped TUI behavior and prevents leaking unrelated agent history into the current agent view.\n",
